#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/actions.php:12
msgid "You do not have permission to run deploy actions."
msgstr "Nu ai permisiunea de a rula actiuni de deploy."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/actions.php:18
msgid "Unknown deploy action."
msgstr "Actiune de deploy necunoscuta."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/actions.php:49
msgid "Testing repository and test action settings are not fully configured."
msgstr ""
"Repository-ul de testare si setarile actiunilor de test nu sunt complet "
"configurate."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/actions.php:55
msgid "Unknown test action."
msgstr "Actiune de test necunoscuta."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/actions.php:69
msgid "Unknown test environment."
msgstr "Environment de test necunoscut."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/actions.php:100
msgid "A workflow was started recently. Wait a moment, then try again."
msgstr ""
"Un workflow a fost pornit recent. Asteapta putin, apoi incearca din nou."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/actions.php:114
msgid ""
"A deploy workflow is already queued or running. Wait for it to finish before "
"starting another action."
msgstr ""
"Un workflow de deploy este deja in coada sau ruleaza. Asteapta sa se termine "
"inainte sa pornesti alta actiune."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/actions.php:129
msgid ""
"A test workflow is already queued or running. Wait for it to finish before "
"starting another action."
msgstr ""
"Un workflow de test este deja in coada sau ruleaza. Asteapta sa se termine "
"inainte sa pornesti alta actiune."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/actions.php:138
msgid ""
"A deploy for this environment was started recently. Wait 2-3 minutes, then "
"try again."
msgstr ""
"Un deploy pentru acest environment a fost pornit recent. Asteapta 2-3 "
"minute, apoi incearca din nou."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/actions.php:152
msgid "A deploy for this environment is already queued or running."
msgstr "Un deploy pentru acest environment este deja in coada sau ruleaza."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/actions.php:184
#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/actions.php:202
msgid "You do not have permission to test the GitHub connection."
msgstr "Nu ai permisiunea de a testa conexiunea GitHub."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/actions.php:221
msgid "You do not have permission to view deploy status."
msgstr "Nu ai permisiunea de a vedea statusul deploy-ului."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/actions.php:228
msgid "Deploy & Test is not fully configured."
msgstr "Deploy & Test nu este configurat complet."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/actions.php:244
msgid "You do not have permission to view test status."
msgstr "Nu ai permisiunea de a vedea statusul testelor."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/actions.php:251
#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/admin/general-tab.php:14
msgid "Testing repository is not fully configured."
msgstr "Repository-ul de testare nu este configurat complet."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/actions.php:267
msgid "You do not have permission to view test summary."
msgstr "Nu ai permisiunea de a vedea summary-ul testului."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/actions.php:277
msgid "Missing test run ID."
msgstr "Lipseste ID-ul rularii de test."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/settings.php:97
msgid "You do not have permission to update deploy settings."
msgstr "Nu ai permisiunea de a actualiza setarile de deploy."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/settings.php:120
msgid "Deploy & Test settings were updated."
msgstr "Setarile de deploy au fost actualizate."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/settings.php:121
msgid "Deploy & Test settings saved."
msgstr "Setarile de deploy au fost salvate."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:15
msgid "General usage"
msgstr "Utilizare generala"

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:19
msgid ""
"Use <strong>Deploy Preview</strong> and <strong>Deploy Production</strong> "
"to trigger the configured deploy workflows from WordPress. Use the "
"<strong>Tests</strong> box to run the configured test actions against the "
"selected test environment."
msgstr ""
"Foloseste <strong>Deploy Preview</strong> si <strong>Deploy Production</"
"strong> pentru a porni workflow-urile de deploy configurate din WordPress. "
"Foloseste boxul <strong>Tests</strong> pentru a rula actiunile de test "
"configurate pe environment-ul selectat."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:23
msgid ""
"The selected Tests on value is sent to GitHub Actions using the input "
"configured in Connection > Test repository. Test buttons can point to the "
"same workflow file with different input values, such as suite=api, suite=ui, "
"or suite=seo."
msgstr ""
"Valoarea selectata la Tests on este trimisa catre GitHub Actions folosind "
"inputul configurat in Connection > Test repository. Butoanele de test pot "
"indica acelasi fisier workflow cu valori diferite, precum suite=api, "
"suite=ui sau suite=seo."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:27
msgid ""
"Deploy and test buttons are locked while any workflow is queued or running, "
"so only one action can run at a time. After starting a test, the page opens "
"Test status automatically and refreshes while the run is active."
msgstr ""
"Butoanele de deploy si test sunt blocate cat timp orice workflow este in "
"coada sau ruleaza, astfel incat sa ruleze o singura actiune odata. Dupa "
"pornirea unui test, pagina deschide automat Test status si se "
"reimprospateaza cat timp rularea este activa."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:31
msgid ""
"Use Deploy status for preview and production deploy results. Use Test status "
"for recent test runs, summary artifacts, and individual passed or failed "
"tests. For full logs and large reports, open the GitHub run."
msgstr ""
"Foloseste Deploy status pentru rezultatele de deploy preview si productie. "
"Foloseste Test status pentru rulari recente de test, artifacte summary si "
"teste individuale trecute sau esuate. Pentru loguri complete si rapoarte "
"mari, deschide rularea din GitHub."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:38
msgid "Creating and Configuring the GitHub App"
msgstr "Crearea si configurarea GitHub App"

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:42
msgid ""
"Log in to GitHub with an account that owns or can administer the "
"organization/repository used for deploys."
msgstr ""
"Autentifica-te in GitHub cu un cont care detine sau poate administra "
"organizatia/repository-ul folosit pentru deploy-uri."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:43
msgid "Open GitHub, then go to <strong>Settings</strong>."
msgstr "Deschide GitHub, apoi mergi la <strong>Settings</strong>."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:44
msgid ""
"Go to <strong>Developer settings</strong>, then <strong>GitHub Apps</strong>."
msgstr ""
"Mergi la <strong>Developer settings</strong>, apoi la <strong>GitHub Apps</"
"strong>."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:45
msgid "Click <strong>New GitHub App</strong>."
msgstr "Apasa <strong>New GitHub App</strong>."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:46
msgid "Use a clear app name that explains the deploy purpose."
msgstr "Foloseste un nume clar pentru app, care explica scopul deploy-ului."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:47
msgid "Set the <strong>Homepage URL</strong> to the WordPress site URL."
msgstr "Seteaza <strong>Homepage URL</strong> la URL-ul site-ului WordPress."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:48
msgid ""
"Leave <strong>Callback URL</strong> empty. This deploy flow does not use "
"GitHub OAuth login."
msgstr ""
"Lasa <strong>Callback URL</strong> gol. Acest flow de deploy nu foloseste "
"login GitHub OAuth."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:49
msgid ""
"Leave <strong>Request user authorization (OAuth) during installation</"
"strong> unchecked."
msgstr ""
"Lasa <strong>Request user authorization (OAuth) during installation</strong> "
"debifat."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:50
msgid "Leave <strong>Enable Device Flow</strong> unchecked."
msgstr "Lasa <strong>Enable Device Flow</strong> debifat."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:51
msgid ""
"Leave <strong>Setup URL</strong> empty and leave <strong>Redirect on update</"
"strong> unchecked."
msgstr ""
"Lasa <strong>Setup URL</strong> gol si <strong>Redirect on update</strong> "
"debifat."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:52
msgid ""
"Leave <strong>Webhook Active</strong> unchecked. Webhooks are not needed for "
"the current deploy status flow."
msgstr ""
"Lasa <strong>Webhook Active</strong> debifat. Webhook-urile nu sunt necesare "
"pentru flow-ul actual de status deploy."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:53
msgid ""
"Under <strong>Repository permissions</strong>, set <strong>Actions</strong> "
"to <strong>Read and write</strong>."
msgstr ""
"La <strong>Repository permissions</strong>, seteaza <strong>Actions</strong> "
"pe <strong>Read and write</strong>."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:54
msgid ""
"Leave all other permissions disabled unless they are explicitly required "
"later."
msgstr ""
"Lasa toate celelalte permisiuni dezactivate, cu exceptia cazului in care vor "
"fi necesare explicit mai tarziu."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:56
msgid ""
"Under <strong>Where can this GitHub App be installed?</strong>, choose "
"<strong>Any account</strong> if the app is created under a personal account "
"but needs to be installed on an organization."
msgstr ""
"La <strong>Where can this GitHub App be installed?</strong>, alege "
"<strong>Any account</strong> daca app-ul este creat sub un cont personal, "
"dar trebuie instalat pe o organizatie."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:58
msgid "Create the GitHub App."
msgstr "Creeaza GitHub App."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:59
msgid "After the app is created, copy the <strong>App ID</strong>."
msgstr "Dupa ce app-ul este creat, copiaza <strong>App ID</strong>."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:60
msgid "Generate a private key and download the <code>.pem</code> file."
msgstr "Genereaza o cheie privata si descarca fisierul <code>.pem</code>."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:61
msgid ""
"Install the app on the organization or account that owns the repository."
msgstr "Instaleaza app-ul pe organizatia sau contul care detine repository-ul."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:62
msgid ""
"Choose <strong>Only select repositories</strong> and select only the "
"repository or repositories connected to this deploy flow."
msgstr ""
"Alege <strong>Only select repositories</strong> si selecteaza doar "
"repository-ul sau repository-urile conectate la acest flow de deploy."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:63
msgid ""
"If the repository belongs to an organization, an organization owner may need "
"to approve or complete the installation."
msgstr ""
"Daca repository-ul apartine unei organizatii, un owner al organizatiei poate "
"fi nevoit sa aprobe sau sa finalizeze instalarea."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:64
msgid ""
"After installation, open the installation page URL and copy the numeric "
"installation ID from the URL."
msgstr ""
"Dupa instalare, deschide URL-ul paginii de instalare si copiaza ID-ul "
"numeric al instalarii din URL."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:68
msgid ""
"Deploy & Test reads deploy status by calling the GitHub API when the admin "
"page loads or refreshes. Webhooks can be added later for real-time status "
"updates, but they require a secure WordPress REST endpoint and webhook "
"secret validation."
msgstr ""
"Deploy & Test citeste statusul deploy-ului apeland GitHub API cand pagina de "
"admin se incarca sau se reimprospateaza. Webhook-urile pot fi adaugate mai "
"tarziu pentru status in timp real, dar necesita un endpoint WordPress REST "
"securizat si validarea unui webhook secret."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:72
msgid "The installation URL usually looks similar to this:"
msgstr "URL-ul instalarii arata de obicei asemanator cu acesta:"

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:78
msgid "In this example, <code>12345678</code> is the installation ID."
msgstr "In acest exemplu, <code>12345678</code> este installation ID."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:82
msgid ""
"<strong>Security notice:</strong> The GitHub App private key must never be "
"committed to a repository, shown in browser JavaScript, or saved in a public "
"folder."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Nota de securitate:</strong> Cheia privata GitHub App nu trebuie "
"niciodata commit-uita intr-un repository, afisata in JavaScript in browser "
"sau salvata intr-un folder public."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:88
msgid "Adding GitHub App Settings to wp-config.php"
msgstr "Adaugarea setarilor GitHub App in wp-config.php"

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:92
msgid ""
"Connect to the server where WordPress is installed and open the <code>wp-"
"config.php</code> file, typically located in the root directory of the "
"WordPress installation."
msgstr ""
"Conecteaza-te la serverul unde este instalat WordPress si deschide fisierul "
"<code>wp-config.php</code>, de obicei aflat in directorul root al instalarii "
"WordPress."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:95
msgid "Add the GitHub App constants before the comment:"
msgstr "Adauga constantele GitHub App inainte de comentariul:"

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:100
msgid ""
"<strong>Recommended option:</strong> store the private key in a separate "
"<code>.pem</code> file and keep only the file path in <code>wp-config.php</"
"code>."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Optiune recomandata:</strong> salveaza cheia privata intr-un fisier "
"<code>.pem</code> separat si pastreaza in <code>wp-config.php</code> doar "
"path-ul catre fisier."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:111
msgid ""
"The <code>.pem</code> file should ideally live outside the public WordPress "
"web root. If that is not possible on the hosting environment, keep it in a "
"protected server folder and make sure it is not committed to Git."
msgstr ""
"Fisierul <code>.pem</code> ar trebui ideal sa fie in afara web root-ului "
"public WordPress. Daca acest lucru nu este posibil pe hosting, pastreaza-l "
"intr-un folder protejat de pe server si asigura-te ca nu este commit-uit in "
"Git."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:114
msgid "Recommended permissions for the private key folder and file:"
msgstr "Permisiuni recomandate pentru folderul si fisierul cheii private:"

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:119
msgid ""
"If WordPress cannot read the private key with those permissions, use this "
"fallback:"
msgstr ""
"Daca WordPress nu poate citi cheia privata cu acele permisiuni, foloseste "
"acest fallback:"

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:125
msgid ""
"Avoid using public read permissions for the private key file unless the "
"hosting environment gives no other option."
msgstr ""
"Evita permisiunile de citire publica pentru fisierul cheii private, cu "
"exceptia cazului in care hostingul nu ofera alta optiune."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:129
msgid ""
"<strong>Fallback option:</strong> place the private key directly in <code>wp-"
"config.php</code>. This works, but it is easier to break because the newline "
"characters must stay correct."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Optiune fallback:</strong> pune cheia privata direct in <code>wp-"
"config.php</code>. Functioneaza, dar este mai usor de stricat, deoarece "
"caracterele newline trebuie sa ramana corecte."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:140
msgid ""
"<strong>Important:</strong> The private key is a production secret. Anyone "
"who has this key and the app IDs can generate temporary GitHub tokens for "
"the repositories where the app is installed."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Important:</strong> Cheia privata este un secret de productie. "
"Oricine are aceasta cheie si ID-urile app-ului poate genera tokenuri GitHub "
"temporare pentru repository-urile unde app-ul este instalat."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:146
msgid "Configuring Workflows"
msgstr "Configurarea workflow-urilor"

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:150
msgid ""
"In the <strong>Connection</strong> tab, set the GitHub owner, deploy "
"repository, testing repository, source refs, target labels, and workflow "
"filenames used by the buttons."
msgstr ""
"In tab-ul <strong>Connection</strong>, seteaza owner-ul GitHub, repository-"
"ul de deploy, repository-ul de testare, source ref-urile, etichetele target "
"si numele fisierelor workflow folosite de butoane."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:161
msgid ""
"The workflow filenames must match files in each repository's <code>.github/"
"workflows</code> directory. Enabled test actions automatically appear as "
"buttons in the General tab."
msgstr ""
"Numele fisierelor workflow trebuie sa corespunda fisierelor din directorul "
"<code>.github/workflows</code> al fiecarui repository. Actiunile de test "
"active apar automat ca butoane in tab-ul General."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:167
msgid "Structuring the Deploy Workflow to Work with the Plugin"
msgstr "Structurarea workflow-ului de deploy ca sa functioneze cu pluginul"

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:171
msgid ""
"The deploy repository should contain one GitHub Actions workflow for preview "
"and one for production, or equivalent workflow files configured in "
"<strong>Connection > Deploy repository</strong>. The plugin triggers these "
"workflows with <code>workflow_dispatch</code>."
msgstr ""
"Repository-ul de deploy ar trebui sa contina un workflow GitHub Actions "
"pentru preview si unul pentru productie, sau fisiere workflow echivalente "
"configurate in <strong>Connection > Deploy repository</strong>. Pluginul "
"porneste aceste workflow-uri cu <code>workflow_dispatch</code>."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:178
msgid ""
"Each deploy workflow should support manual dispatch and deploy the ref "
"configured in the plugin."
msgstr ""
"Fiecare workflow de deploy trebuie sa suporte pornire manuala si sa faca "
"deploy pentru ref-ul configurat in plugin."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:203
msgid "For production, use a separate workflow file and a clear workflow name:"
msgstr ""
"Pentru productie, foloseste un fisier workflow separat si un nume clar "
"pentru workflow:"

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:228
msgid ""
"Recommended plugin settings: <code>Preview workflow file</code> should point "
"to <code>deploy-preview.yml</code>, and <code>Production workflow file</"
"code> should point to <code>deploy-production.yml</code>. Use names like "
"<code>Deploy Preview</code> and <code>Deploy Production</code> so the status "
"cards can classify recent runs correctly."
msgstr ""
"Setari recomandate in plugin: <code>Preview workflow file</code> ar trebui "
"sa indice <code>deploy-preview.yml</code>, iar <code>Production workflow "
"file</code> ar trebui sa indice <code>deploy-production.yml</code>. "
"Foloseste nume precum <code>Deploy Preview</code> si <code>Deploy "
"Production</code>, ca status cards sa poata clasifica corect rularile "
"recente."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:232
msgid ""
"Keep deploy workflows idempotent and safe to re-run. The plugin locks deploy "
"and test buttons while any workflow is queued or running, but the workflow "
"itself should still handle retries safely."
msgstr ""
"Pastreaza workflow-urile de deploy idempotente si sigure la rerulare. "
"Pluginul blocheaza butoanele de deploy si test cat timp orice workflow este "
"in coada sau ruleaza, dar workflow-ul in sine trebuie totusi sa gestioneze "
"retry-urile in siguranta."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:238
msgid "Structuring the Test Framework to Work with the Plugin"
msgstr "Structurarea test framework-ului ca sa functioneze cu pluginul"

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:242
msgid ""
"The testing repository should expose a manually dispatched GitHub Actions "
"workflow with inputs that match the buttons configured in <strong>Connection "
"> Test repository</strong>."
msgstr ""
"Repository-ul de testare trebuie sa expuna un workflow GitHub Actions pornit "
"manual, cu inputuri care corespund butoanelor configurate in "
"<strong>Connection > Test repository</strong>."

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:259
msgid "Recommended Deploy & Test settings for that workflow:"
msgstr "Setari Deploy & Test recomandate pentru acel workflow:"

#: wordpress-deploy-and-test-plugin/deploy-and-test/includes/how-to-use-page/how-to-use-page.php:268
msgid ""
"Every test run should upload a small JSON summary artifact with this "
"predictable name:"
